#!/usr/bin/env testml


*jsc.validate(*json) == *valid


=== Test 1 - validation of Relative JSON Pointers (RJP) - a valid upwards RJP
--- valid: true
--- jsc
{"format": "relative-json-pointer"}
--- json
"1"


=== Test 2 - validation of Relative JSON Pointers (RJP) - a valid downwards RJP
--- valid: true
--- ^jsc
--- json
"0/foo/bar"


=== Test 3 - validation of Relative JSON Pointers (RJP) - a valid up and then down RJP, with array index
--- valid: true
--- ^jsc
--- json
"2/0/baz/1/zip"


=== Test 4 - validation of Relative JSON Pointers (RJP) - a valid RJP taking the member or index name
--- valid: true
--- ^jsc
--- json
"0#"


=== Test 5 - validation of Relative JSON Pointers (RJP) - an invalid RJP that is a valid JSON Pointer
--- valid: false
--- ^jsc
--- json
"/foo/bar"


